SCHECKER, Appellant, v. WOOLSEY, Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. January 13, 1893.) Appeal from special term, New York county. Action by William H. Schecker against Edward J. Woolsey for breach of contract. From an order refusing to advance case on short cause calendar, plaintiff appeals. Affirmed.

*1121Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and O’BRIEN and FOLLETT, JJ.

Cannon & Atwater, (Henry G. Atwater, of counsel,) for appellant. Howe & Hummel, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

The order should be affirmed, with §10 costs and disbursements.
